# Project Philosophy

- Build systems that are predictable, testable, and hard to misuse.
- Write production-ready, clean, maintainable code.
- Prefer clarity over cleverness.
- Avoid overengineering.
- Follow the existing project structure and style.
- Do not introduce unnecessary abstractions.
- Reuse existing modules whenever possible.
- Keep consistency with the rest of the codebase.
